      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: preserve user text that looks like inbound metadata",
        "body": "Closes #95279\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where users who paste or quote text that looks like OpenClaw's inbound metadata blocks would have real user content stripped, deduplicated, or replayed incorrectly across chat history, memory export, and historical prompt replay.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis change adds a trusted host-owned bare-body contract on persisted user turns and teaches downstream consumers to prefer that trusted body over forgeable sentinel stripping. Legacy sentinel stripping stays in place only as a fallback for older rows that do not carry the trusted field, and runtime persistence now preserves or clears the trusted field instead of inventing one from decorated-looking text.\n\n## User Impact\n\nQuoted inbound-metadata text now stays visible when it is real user content, while newly persisted inbound-decorated turns still replay, dedupe, and export with their canonical bare body. Older transcript rows keep their existing heuristic cleanup path.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/sessions/user-turn-transcript.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs ui/src/ui/chat/message-extract.test.ts ui/src/ui/chat/message-normalizer.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/strip-inbound-meta.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/prompt-prelude.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs packages/memory-host-sdk/src/host/session-files.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/session-tool-result-guard.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.llm-boundary.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/run/attempt.llm-boundary.cache-stability.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/cli-session-history.test.ts src/infra/session-cost-usage.test.ts`\n- `pnpm build`\n",
        "branch": "codex/issue-95279-inbound-decoration-contract",
